node.text: This interview, hosted by @coachdhillon (give him a follow!), covers how I built the @investearnsave page into a profitable business in just 1 year, as well as my thoughts on themes such as investing, education and self-development. It was a pleasure to be on his podcast and we decided to share it here to give it extra visibility.

node.text:
Money is something you only respect when you've experienced it's scarcity...⁣
⁣
Whilst most of us don't need to be told that, we're not the children of billionaires, we can learn something from this about money.⁣
⁣
Once we've achieved basic comforts and financial security, having more money won't make us happier, however the pursuit of it might.⁣
⁣
If you pick a business model, investing strategy, career that you enjoy. You will find increasing your wealth to be much more enjoyable than actually having that extra money.⁣
⁣
If you're struggling right now, you might not believe this logic but once you've reached a place where you're financially secure, you'll see it for yourself.⁣
⁣
This is why you should pick ways of making money that are meaningful and enjoyable to you. If you pursue money in a way you despise doing, money will simply make you unhappy.⁣
⁣
Love the process, not the reward.⁣
⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
This post may be a little cringy, but there is an important message so give the caption a read...⁣
⁣
Football (soccer for my American followers) is a great place to study the impact of mentality on success because it's so obvious to see.⁣
⁣
There's those players with obvious talent that have a bad game/a setback and their career flops from there.⁣
⁣
Then, there's people with a mentality like Ronaldo who can have big setbacks and then come back better than ever.⁣
⁣
Even recently, in the game where he became the leading international goal scorer, he missed a penalty near the start of the game. Then, he scored 2 goals near the end of the game to win it.⁣
⁣
That is the evidence of a winner's mentality.⁣
⁣
You need to incorporate this into your own mentality.⁣
⁣
Both entrepreneurs and investors will have big set backs, particularly in the start of their journey that will make them want to quit. ⁣
⁣
You will decide "business isn't for me" or "investing is all a scam" and give up because of one bad moment.⁣
⁣
But winner's will learn from their failure, and come back stronger and better. They will improve their investing strategy, come back with a better business model.⁣
⁣
And they will succeed.⁣
⁣
Will you be the Ronaldo of your niche, or just another wonderkid who never reached their potential? ⁣
⁣
Congratulations to #CR7 on breaking the International Goalscoring record!⁣
⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#ronaldo #cristianoronaldo #success #winningmentality #winnersmentality #mentality

⁣
These people are happy and wealthy.⁣
⁣
These people inspire others to become wealthy.⁣
⁣
These are the kinds of people you want to aspire to be.⁣

node.text:
Yes, if your brand is looking like this, it can be a good decision, but unless you're a rapper or other entertainer, stop trying to look so rich...⁣
⁣
Focus on actually becoming rich.⁣
⁣
Focus on buying back your time with your investments.⁣
⁣
Focus on important purchases like your home, travel, providing for family, etc.⁣
⁣
Nobody cares if you're wearing Gucci.⁣
⁣
Only person you want to dress to impress for is your accountant. Few will understand.⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣

node.text:
Some variation of this is something all entrepreneurs experience...⁣
⁣
You also have a rollercoaster of perceptions too.⁣
⁣
At first you think a certain goal will make you feel happy and successful, and for a short time when you reach it you will.⁣
⁣
Then you end up networking with people doing way better than you and you see you have far to go.⁣
⁣
Then you hit some kind of roadblock, maybe you have a bad month or an event affects your business, you feel like you've completely failed then even though you're still way ahead of where you were when you first started.⁣
⁣
You just need to learn to remove yourself from the situation, meditate on it and realise as long as you're putting in the work to progress, that's all that matters.⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
